}
```

## Chart & Visualization Guidelines

### Chart Colors
```css
/* Primary chart line/area */
--chart-primary: var(--color-slate-500);
--chart-primary-light: var(--color-slate-300);

/* Success/Growth trends */
--chart-success: var(--color-emerald-500);
--chart-success-light: var(--color-emerald-200);

/* Decline trends */
--chart-decline: var(--color-rose-500);
--chart-decline-light: var(--color-rose-200);

/* Secondary data */
--chart-secondary: var(--color-blue-gray-400);
--chart-grid: var(--color-slate-200);
```

### Chart Styling
- **Grid lines**: Subtle slate-200, minimal opacity
- **Axes**: slate-400 for labels, slate-300 for lines
- **Data points**: 4px radius, semi-transparent fill
- **Hover states**: Increased opacity, subtle shadow
- **Tooltips**: White background, slate-700 text, subtle shadow

### Chart Types
- **Net Worth Line Chart**: Primary trend line with area fill
- **Asset/Liability Bar Chart**: Comparative bars with muted colors
- **Category Breakdown**: Donut charts with sequential slate tones

